    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 27, 1896</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Feb. 7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 586.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On Saturday last I telegraphed you the substance
                    of the reply received at the foreign office, through the colonial office, to the
                    inquiry made by me under your instructions as to the condition of the American
                        <pb facs="0664" n="570" xml:id="pg_570"/> citizens held under arrest by the
                    Boer Government at the Transvaal for alleged participation in Dr. Jameson’s
                    invasion.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>The courtesy and promptness with which Her Majesty’s officials responded to our
                    inquiries respecting our countrymen is certainly marked and gratifying, and I
                    have not omitted to make acknowledgment in terms.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
